-- Pinera Approval Rating Fell to 29% in March, Chile Poll Shows
-- B y   R a n d a l l   W o o d s
-- 2012-04-04T14:20:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-04/pinera-approval-rating-fell-to-29-in-march-chile-poll-shows.html
Chilean President Sebastian Pinera’s
approval rating fell to 29 percent in March, Santiago-based
research group Adimark GfK said in a report today.  His approval rating was 33 percent in February, the group
said in a report published March 5. Today’s poll of 1,469 people
has a margin of error of plus or minus 2.6 percentage points,
Adimark said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Randall Woods in Santiago at 
 rwoods13@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 